org.apache.freemarker.core.model

Interface TemplateFunctionModel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    TemplateCallableModel, TemplateModel
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    JavaMethodModel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourceBundleModel, SimpleJavaMethodModel

    public interface TemplateFunctionModel
extends TemplateCallableModel
    A TemplateCallableModel, which returns its result as a TemplateModel at the end of its execution. This is in contrast with TemplateDirectiveModel, which writes its result progressively to the output, if it has output at all. Also, TemplateFunctionModel-s can only be called where an expression is expected. (If some future template languages allows calling functions outside expression context, on the top-level, then that's a shorthand to doing that in with interpolation, like ${f()}.)

    Example usage in templates: < a href="${my.toProductURL(product.id)}">, <#list my.groupByFirstLetter(products, property="name") as productGroup>

    You can find utilities for implementing TemplateFunctionModel-s in CallableUtils.

      • getFunctionArgumentArrayLayout

        ArgumentArrayLayout getFunctionArgumentArrayLayout()
        Returns the argument array layout to use when calling the {@link #execute(TemplateModel[], CallPlace, Environment)} method, or rarely null. If it's null then there can only be positional arguments, any number of them (though of course the execute method implementation itself may restricts the acceptable argument count), and the argument array will be simply as long as the number of arguments specified at the call place. This layoutless mode is for example used by JavaMethodModel-s.
